n class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udalariansilvershade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalarian Silvershade</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 2:43:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm</span><hr size=1> Well, at 41 (and admittedly a bit over equipped) with tanks several levels higher (44-46~) unless they are using two decent speed weapons and haste, I'm hitting evade every time it pops up, and even then getting beat on pretty bad sometimes. Yes, I know about distance etc..but when I evade, succeed, still get hit, back out of combat range, watch the mob turn to the tank, move back in and get smacked before I turn attack back on...<br>
other times I hit it once and never worry about it for the rest of the fight (admittedly alot more rare).<br>
<br>
I can see this being both good and bad - good because it will let you 'ping-pong' the mob easier, tank for 95% of the time, evade onto shammy et al for BS, the monster turns back to you. Bad for the situation I described first - not real keen on swapping out my sash for a AC belt because I swing too fast and I'm winding up the primary tank.<br>
<br>
<br>
Is there a way to code this so it would be conditional upon the hate list reaching a certain # of players? Since this seems to be the root of the problem (the hate list going from 6 to 60), have it so once 'x' people are on the list evade is modified to only drop 33% instead of a fixed value, and then up the fixed value slightly (just above the wandering into range value) so whatever freaky KC pathing/aggro bug that happens thrice in a blue moon will only happen once in said blue moon. I can see this really hurting rogues grouped with tanks who are already having a tough time taunting off them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulurik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurik</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 2:58:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmmm</span><hr size=1> &quot;We looked at Rogues, saw an oversight in the way Evade worked, and we proposed a change that will not in any way ruin the class, nor make them less powerful, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> but will make them responsible for more of their damage output.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
A little vague here, Kendrick. Do you mean to make us responsible as to how much damage we do? Meaning, If I see that I just backstabbed for 300, and quad'd for 150+ damage, I better turn auto attack off and &quot;be responsible&quot; for my damage?<br>
<br>
Are you wanting for rogues to regulate their own damage output?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><P><u><font face="Roman" size="+1" color="Navy"><b>Lurik Crim'Tal</b></font></u><BR>
<b><font face="Roman" size="-1" color="Black">Proud leader of the Veiled Alliance<BR>
Apprentice of Nimbel Fyngers and Zappalan Greymist<BR>
Server Rodcet Nife</font><BR><BR><font color="green">"DEFINATELY get your mask, it's still worth having even if we both are superior Dark Elves already." - Durden Darkpoint</b></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anaia>Anaia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 3:12:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Evade changes sound good...but add these to it.</span><hr size=1> Personally, I really dont understand why evade was ever combined with the hide skill.  It seems to me that Evade as proposed to work with the new percentage reduction in hate would function much better as a stand alone skill that improves/reduces the percentange of hate reduction as the skill improves.  Given that hide/sneak is somewhat comperable (though not identical) to the invisibility spell in effect why wouldnt casters casting invis on themselves or another person reduce/remove hate?  I think the point is that it wouldnt.  Evade was of course added because it was needed, yet it seems that perhaps given the thought going into the skill at this moment that some consideration should be made as to why it is not an actual 'skill'.<br>
<br>
Furthermore if Evade were uncoupled from the Hide skill, I would like to see some changes made to Hide to address the total lack of need to pursue skill increases much beyond 80 (the point at which constant success is almost a guarantee).  Perhaps it would make sense to allow the Hide skill - beyond current abilitie to remove visibility - to also provide a percentage chance to make a mob with hate &quot;forget&quot; you. This would completely remove you from the hate list and provide you the ability to not have to zone to remove aggro's effects.  Obviously this percentage would be contingent on the level of the monster and perhaps the amount of current hate you have accumulated.  If mob A has been beaten to a pulp by a backstabbing rogue, its highly unlikely that he will completely forget about him w/o the rogue having amazing abilities to HIDE to extents that prevent the mob from finding him.   Given the right circumstances the rogue could then conceveably successfully 'Evade' from combat (reducing the hate) and then attempt to 'Hide' to get the hell out of there.  So the big question is how can this be abused.  Frankly if implemented right...'Hide' to remove hate would be successful in my mind only 1 out of 6 or so tries vs a monster with say 50% hate and equal level.  I can see this giving a rogue the opportunity to maybe get it to go off when trying to flee.  <br>
<br>
Finally, I really think that the above changes to Hide can eliminate the silliness of the train that runs to the zone and says 'aw shucks...we didnt get that warrior in time before he zoned' from turning around and saying....'well...we'll just stroll on back to that rogue who we still hate and beat him up some'.   At some point there needs to be a mechanisim for a rogue to get out of danger...we dont have the HP's of tanks...cant gate, evac or SoW like casters...so why not do something similar yet uniquely different to feign death. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeffindagrifter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geffin Dagrifter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 4:14:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evade changes sound good...but add these to it.</span><hr size=1> Absor just posted this in the Rogue Talk:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
We've decided on another tack for changing Evade.<br>
<br>
Instead of setting you to 120 (current Evade), or reducing your total hate by 33% (our first intended change), this is what we are thinking of doing.<br>
<br>
If the rogue is #1 on the hate list, a successful evade will lower his hate to a point between the 2nd and 3rd person on the hate list.<br>
<br>
If the rogue is NOT #1 on the hate list, a successful evade will lower the total hate by a few percent, allowing &quot;pre-evade&quot; to remain a viable tactic.<br>
<br>
At no time will Evade increase a rogue's hate, it will always reduce it. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This sounds much better to me as it will always have a successful evade turn the mob, barring lag. I was getting worried that I would have to try to stay within that 33% above the main tank.<br>
